`Screens.jsx` and `contents.js` are imported by BedroomSlice but kept as separate files (overlays + data, not game logic).

## Hard rules
- Game code goes in `BedroomSlice.jsx` only
- No Tailwind — not installed, don't use classes
- No UI libraries — no Radix, no shadcn, nothing. Inline styles + canvas only.
- Do NOT import: react-query, wouter, framer-motion, recharts, zod
- Layout tweaks → edit `layout.json`, not BedroomSlice.jsx
- Do NOT split BedroomSlice.jsx yet (in-flight work from other sessions)
- Do NOT touch files outside `artifacts/pack-it-up/`

## Sprite pattern
```js
const CELL = 4; // 1 sprite px = 4 screen px
const r = (ctx, color, x, y, w=1, h=1) => { ctx.fillStyle=color; ctx.fillRect(x,y,w,h); }
// Use colors from the P palette at top of file
```

## Git discipline
Always pull before starting. Always commit when done. Multiple AI sessions run concurrently.
